{# Template: mcda/mcda-convergence-check.j2 #}
{# goal: Compute normalized convergence metric for MCDA cycles. #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
verbosity = "terse"
max_tokens = 1000
thinking_budget = "standard"

Compute convergence where 0 means ranking confidence is high and sensitivity analysis shows acceptable robustness.

Input:
```json
{
  "ranking_result": {{ ranking_result | tojson }},
  "sensitivity_result": {{ sensitivity_result | tojson }}
}
```

You are a convergence evaluator. Measure convergence on [0,1] where 0 means ranking confidence is high and sensitivity analysis shows acceptable robustness.

## Context
- Convergence threshold: {{ _convergence.threshold | default(0.15) }}
- Iteration: {{ _convergence.iterations_completed | default(0) }} / {{ _convergence.max_iterations | default(3) }}
- Improvement target: {{ _convergence.improvement_target | default(0.10) }}

## Convergence Method
0 = fully converged (ranking confidence is high and sensitivity analysis shows acceptable robustness). 1 = not converged. Score how much work remains.

Return JSON only:
```json
{
  "convergence_metric": 0.0,
  "convergence_method": "LLM-assessed saturation detection",
  "rationale": "short explanation",
  "blockers": []
}
```
